The Lady Panthers won the 2nd Region All A Tournament and will play as a team. Golf team members are Byrlee Spurlin, Maddie Huddleston, Natalie Oldham and Maddie Back.

We are proud of all of our golf team members on their hard work this season.

post_text:
August 30, 2020
For Immediate Release

Due to ongoing health and safety concerns and the increasing COVID-19 cases in Kentucky and nationally, the Dawson Springs Board of Education will have a special virtual (online) Board meeting on Monday, August 3rd at 6pm. The main topic of this meeting will be to discuss and potentially approve school starting on September 1, 2020 for students using virtual remote instruction. This would have students working and learning from home as they are instructed by their teacher(s) from school. Wi-fi capable computers will be available for students to “check out” from school if needed. Much more information and specifics will follow in the coming weeks.

The agenda for this virtual meeting will be posted shortly on the district Kentucky School Board Association (KSBA) portal. It can be found here: https://portal.ksba.org/public/Agency.aspx?PublicAgencyID=47&AgencyTypeID=1

The special virtual Board meeting on Monday as mentioned above will also be streamed live on the district Facebook page.

ATTENTION 3 & 4 YEAR OLD PARENTS/GUARDIANS:
If you are interested in your child attending Dawson Springs Preschool in the fall of 2020, please let us know via:

Phone 270-797-2991, ext. 1004,
Email kristin.merrill@dawsonsprings.kyschools.us
or Dawson Springs Preschool Facebook page Messenger.

PreK Eligibility:
•4 years old on or before August 1, 2020 and whose family is 160% of the poverty level or below.
OR
•3 years old on or before August 1, 2020 with a suspected delay.
In your message please include:
*Child’s name
*Date of Birth
*Address
*Phone number
*Parent/Guardian Name
*Any suspected delays and if you feel your family might
be income eligible for our preschool program.

Once you contact us, we will reach out to you about picking up an enrollment packet.

Thank you and we look forward to hearing from you soon!
Dawson Springs Preschool

Dear Parent and Community Members,

Dawson Springs Independent School System would appreciate your help. Your input is vital in the planning and implementation of the student support and academic enrichment in our school. Specifically, to provide all students with access to a well-rounded education, improve school conditions for student learning and improve the use of technology to improve the academic achievement and digital literacy of all students. We appreciate your feedback and thank you for taking the time to complete this survey. https://forms.gle/DdGcq4BU3BbGDJPM8

Sincerely,

Dawson Springs School System

Message from Principal Jennifer Ward about Locker Items Pick-up and Textbook/Library Book Drop-Offs

Administration will be cleaning out lockers and placing personal items in bags (with student name) for parent pick up.

Pick-up will be in front of the elementary building from 9:00 to 11:00. Please form a line of cars out front as we do for student pick-up/drop-off. Someone will be there to hand a student bag through the car window. We ask that all parents and students remain in the vehicle as no students or parents will be allowed in the building during this time.

○Preschool will pick-up on May 5th from 9:00 AM – 10:30 AM
○Kindergarten will pick-up on May 5th from 11:00 – 1:00 PM
○1st Grade will pick-up on May 6th from 9:00 AM – 10:30 AM
○2nd Grade will pick-up on May 6th from 11:00 – 1:00 PM
○3rd Grade will pick-up on May 8th from 9:00 AM – 10:30 AM

○5th Grade will pick-up on May 11th from 9:00 AM – 10:30 AM

post_text:
Surprise Senior Announcement:
Through a collaborative effort with Mayor Chris Smiley, Our Senior Class Sponsors, Dawson Springs PTO, and Gerald Printing, we will be able to hang banners of the seniors throughout the City of Dawson Springs in the weeks to come. The printed banners will have our seniors' formal portrait. The banners aren't ready yet but once they are printed, Mayor Smiley will help to make sure they are on display for all to see. This is just another example why it's great to be a panther! Thank you Mayor Smiley, Senior Class Sponsors, Dawson Springs PTO, and Gerald Printing for helping to provide this opportunity. #LivePurple

YLA (Young Leaders In Action) Mental Health Survey
This survey is anonymous, please don't put anything non-related of the topic of the question you are answering in the space provided below. We thank you for taking our survey. We encourage you to speak with our school counselor or a trusted adult if you are struggling or may be in need of help. post_text: Congratulations to the Boys Cross Country team and coach Rhonda Simpson on winning the Class 1A Regional Cross Country meet held at Marshall County. This is the first time the boys have won the regional meet. They will run on Saturday, November 2nd at the Horse Park in Lexington, Ky. Athletes and placement: Yosiyah McCune 8th, Tyler Hale 10th, Ethan Osborne 11th, Caleb Garrett 12th, Lucas Osborne 13th Michael Faughn 23rd and Logan McKnight 24th. Also qualifying from the girls team and earning a trip to the state meet were Vanessa Tackett and Kimberly Hoover, coached by Wayne Simpson. Congratulations to all runners and coaches on a great season.
